The occurrence of a new influenza virus subtype in 1997 in Hongkong caused only minor outbreaks due to the swift and determined actions of the institutions involved. However, this incident again made it clear that an influenza pandemic is still a pending threat. As a result the WHO presented a pandemic preparedness plan which is to facilitate the global measures taken to fight an imminent or ongoing pandemic. Strong efforts of influenza surveillance and the coordination of worldwide measures are essential to this plan. Furthermore the WHO suggested the developement and introduction of similar national preparedness plans.  
